author: Igor Hrcek
comment: I like how it looks, modern and fresh. But, there is a problem with usability. For example I have around 20 services and the page scroll is just enormous. It would be nice to have ability to change layout to have two tokens in a single row. Also, fingerprint security or pin are needed in app like this, please implement.

author: Dale Wells
comment: In need of some more icons for distinguishability.  The accounts aren't labelled at the top level, this just creates an added step of having to long press the account to find out which it is.  Either more logos for other services (Google is literally the only one in my list of 8 accounts that has an icon) or add some generic icons for things like email. Even better, add the account names to the main page above the email address. The email address alone is not sufficient

reply.author: overmorrow
reply.content:
Hey Dale,

thanks for your feedback! You're completely right and Thenticate needs more icons. That's why the upcoming release will come with more than 100 different logos and generic icons 😉

Warm greetings from Germany!

author: Quirijn Groot Bluemink
comment: Great app! but it become a hassle to use if you have a lot of codes. Maybe being able to categorise them? Or having a smaller grid instead of a list

author: Mark Schauer
comment: This is probably the best-looking OTP generator I've seen. At first, I thought there wasn't a timer (a basic feature to know if your code is about to expire), but then I realized that the color fades the closer the code is to resetting.  At the moment, this a four-star app. I would love to see the ability to add our own custom icons because right now, there are only about 30 built-in ones. That means a majority of my OTP codes have the generic star. That makes it a bit hard to differentiate between the codes. To remedy this, instead of inputting my login the OTP is associated with, I input the website. Not ideal.  Furthermore, I'd like to see the addition of custom groups or labels, and a search function. If any/all of these are implemented, I'll update this review to five stars.

author: Richard Rosner
comment: Great app. Beautiful design and great backup solution. But it's crashing when trying to manually set up a new token do you have to manually create a QR code with all the information

A whole lot of room for improvement here. The good: this is the most beautiful 2FA app I've ever seen. And it performs quite well.  The bad: the limited list of icons for services makes it difficult to tell what stuff some stuff is. Perhaps being able to select a custom vector or image would help. The list is extremely inefficient when you have a lot of accounts. Items being more compact would be much appreciated.  The ugly: accounts in the list view only show the email it's under, omitting the service it's for.

comment: I like the design, but the customisation options are unfortunately limited.
